    "id": "msg_001",
    "channel_id": "ch_001",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "Hello everyone. My granddaughter Emma pointed me here. I picked up watercolor a few months ago and I'm still very much a beginner. Glad to be learning alongside you all.",
    "timestamp": "2024-11-06T10:12:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_002",
    "channel_id": "ch_001",
    "author_id": "500100200300400008",
    "author_username": "Nora Petrakis",
    "content": "Welcome, Juan! You'll fit right in. Don't be shy about posting your practice pieces, that's how we all learn here.",
    "timestamp": "2024-11-06T11:40:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_003",
    "channel_id": "ch_003",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "Beginner question: my washes keep drying with hard edges instead of a smooth gradient. Am I using too little water, or is it my paper?",
    "timestamp": "2025-01-18T14:05:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_004",
    "channel_id": "ch_003",
    "author_id": "500100200300400006",
    "author_username": "Wren Delacroix",
    "content": "Usually two things: wet the paper evenly first, and work fast before it starts to set. Cold-press cotton paper also blends far more forgivingly than student-grade cellulose.",
    "timestamp": "2025-01-18T15:22:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_005",
    "channel_id": "ch_003",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "That helps a great deal, thank you Wren. I was letting the first layer dry too long before floating in the next color.",
    "timestamp": "2025-01-19T09:30:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_006",
    "channel_id": "ch_002",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "Finished my first proper landscape this weekend, a stand of pines along the Severn River. The sky finally came out soft. Feedback welcome.",
    "timestamp": "2025-03-09T16:45:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_007",
    "channel_id": "ch_002",
    "author_id": "500100200300400012",
    "author_username": "Gloria Santos",
    "content": "Juan, that sky is lovely and calm. The reflections in the water sell the whole scene. Big improvement from your practice washes.",
    "timestamp": "2025-03-09T18:20:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_008",
    "channel_id": "ch_002",
    "author_id": "500100200300400023",
    "author_username": "Adele Morrison",
    "content": "Agreed, the edges of those pines are nice and loose. If you want more depth next time, drop a touch more pigment into the foreground trees while they're still damp.",
    "timestamp": "2025-03-10T08:15:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_009",
    "channel_id": "ch_004",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "Question for the group on supplies: is a round 8 and a round 12 enough to start, or should I add a flat brush for skies?",
    "timestamp": "2025-05-14T11:00:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_010",
    "channel_id": "ch_004",
    "author_id": "500100200300400010",
    "author_username": "Helen Cho",
    "content": "A 3/4 inch flat is worth it just for skies and large washes. You can do a lot with those three brushes for a good while.",
    "timestamp": "2025-05-14T12:35:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_011",
    "channel_id": "ch_002",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "Shared a small piece of the Naval Academy seawall at dawn. Tried the wet-on-wet sky Wren described. Much smoother this time.",
    "timestamp": "2025-12-02T15:10:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_012",
    "channel_id": "ch_002",
    "author_id": "500100200300400005",
    "author_username": "Tomás Okafor",
    "content": "You can really see the technique clicking, Juan. That graded sky is exactly what wet-on-wet is for. Nicely done.",
    "timestamp": "2025-12-02T17:48:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_013",
    "channel_id": "ch_005",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "For those who paint outdoors, how do you keep your palette from drying out too fast on a breezy day by the water?",
    "timestamp": "2025-10-04T10:20:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_014",
    "channel_id": "ch_005",
    "author_id": "500100200300400022",
    "author_username": "Vincent Caruso",
    "content": "A small spray bottle and a palette with a lid helps a lot. I mist every few minutes when it's windy. Working in shade slows it down too.",
    "timestamp": "2025-10-04T11:55:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_015",
    "channel_id": "ch_003",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "How do you all handle mixing greens that don't look artificial? Mine come out too vivid for the trees I'm painting.",
    "timestamp": "2026-02-11T13:40:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_016",
    "channel_id": "ch_003",
    "author_id": "500100200300400003",
    "author_username": "Priya Nadkarni",
    "content": "Skip the tube greens and mix your own from a blue and a yellow, then knock it back with a touch of its complement or a bit of burnt sienna. Much more natural for foliage.",
    "timestamp": "2026-02-11T14:30:00-05:00",
    "pinned": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_017",
    "channel_id": "ch_002",
    "author_id": "500100200300400001",
    "author_username": "Juan Hernandez",
    "content": "Finished a marsh scene at golden hour using the mixed greens tip. Framed this one for the wall. Thank you all for the patient advice over the past year.",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-23T16:05:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
  {
    "id": "msg_018",
    "channel_id": "ch_002",
    "author_id": "500100200300400006",
    "author_username": "Wren Delacroix",
    "content": "This is frame-worthy indeed, Juan. Warm light, believable greens, confident edges. Wonderful progress. Keep them coming.",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-23T19:12:00-04:00",
    "pinned": "false"
  },
